backgroundInformationList.description: Notice of Passing of By-law - 260 King Street East

contact.contactName: Toronto and East York Community Council

noticeDescription: Take notice that the Council of the City of Toronto has passed By-law 929-2020 to designate 260 King Street East (Toronto Centre, Ward 13) as being of cultural heritage value or interest.

otherReferenceList.description: By-law 929-2020 - To amend By-law 855-88, being a by-law to designate the property at 260 King Street East as being of cultural heritage value or interest, to include the building on the property with the entrance addresses of 254, 256 and 266 King Street East, 427 and 435 Adelaide Street East, and 157 Princess Street, and to revise the legal description.
